engaged gear detected from the AGS sytem
Voltage of barrel possition sensor. Main sensor for AGS system
information byte which gives an overview of the shift progress
If an shift is requested and will be done the bit up or down will be set until the shift is complete ready. These Bit also works like a trigger for the data aquisition system.
When a shift is requested, the target engine speed is the calculated value of the engine rpm after the succeded shift. If no shift is requested targed engine speed is the same as engine speed.
